President Trump addressed the 2017 Values Voter Summit in Washington, D.C. In his speech, he expressed condolences for the victims of the Las Vegas shooting and praised the bravery of those who risked their lives to save others. He also acknowledged the recent natural disasters in California, Puerto Rico, and the Gulf Coast, and pledged support for those affected. Trump emphasized the importance of religious liberty and defended the rights of faith-based organizations. He also spoke about his administration's accomplishments, such as the appointment of Justice Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court, the reinstatement of the Mexico City Policy, and the protection of religious freedom. Trump highlighted his efforts to combat terrorism and praised the strength and resilience of the American people. He concluded by reaffirming his commitment to defending America's values and freedoms.